Secondly, note here how he breakes his promiſe: he promiſed immediately before to be breefe & to bring that which remayned into a ſhort ſumme;
〈◊〉
& yet he is now more large and ample in laying out this teſtimony of Mr. B. then in any of the former. In this dealing it ſeemes he ſcarſe knew or cared what he ſayd or did.
